               <msContents>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="MS_Bodl_712-item1">
                     <locus from="1">(fol. 1)</locus>
                     <author key="person_61539765">Bede</author>
                     <title key="work_968">Historia ecclesiastica</title>
                     <colophon>Explicit liber qui uocatur Beda de gestis Anglorum,
                        scriptus reuerendo domino domino Roberto de Wiuill episcopo Sarisburiensi</colophon><rubric>Ecclesiastica hystoria gentis
                        Anglorum</rubric><rubric>In five books, with preface and lists of chapters. The miniature
                        on fol. 1 is a figure of Bede, book in hand. See T. D. Hardy's
                        <title>Descriptive Catalogue</title> i (1862), p. 439.</rubric>
                     <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="2" xml:id="MS_Bodl_712-item2">
                     <locus from="89">(fol. 89)</locus>
                     <author key="person_205295992">William of Malmesbury</author>
                     <title key="work_5072">Gesta regum Anglorum</title>
                     <rubric>Gesta Anglorum secundum Willelmum Malmesburiensem</rubric>
                     <note>In six
                        books to 1128. [The text is that of the second edition. Cr.] This and the
                        next two articles have small miniatures of the authors writing or reading
                        their works, etc. See Hardy ut supra, ii (1865), p. 160; Stubbs, W.
                        Malmesbiriensis, Rolls Series, p. lxxviii. Cr.]</note>
                     
                     <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="3" xml:id="MS_Bodl_712-item3">
                     <locus from="199">(fol. 199)</locus>
                     <author key="person_2614028">Martin of Troppau</author>
                     <title key="work_3115">Chronica pontificum et imperatorum</title>
                     <rubric>Incipit Cronica fratris Martini penitentiarii domini
                        pape [erased] &amp; capellani</rubric><finalRubric>Explicit Cronica Martini de papis
                        [erased] &amp; imperatoribus</finalRubric><note>With preface.</note>
                     
                     <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="#historica" n="4" xml:id="MS_Bodl_712-item4">
                     <locus from="249">(fol. 249)</locus>
                     <title key="work_10955" type="desc">Chronicle of <placeName key="place_7002445">England</placeName>, 449–1269</title>
                     <rubric>Hic incipit Cronica de adventu Anglorum in Britanniam secundum
                        Bedam Anglorum istoriographum</rubric>
                     <note>From 449 to 1066; followed at fol. 259v by a
                        second part, 'Incipit Cronica de aduentu Normannorum in Angliam &amp; de
                        vltimo conquesto' 1066-1269, but part is lost, and the MS. ends abruptly in
                        1269 with 'quod sede uacante pertinet ad ' with catchword 'capitulum': the
                        running-head throughout is 'Cronica Bede'. The two parts begin respectively:</note><incipit>
                        Angli Saxones Marciani principis tempore</incipit><incipit>Ut sciatur origo cause quare
                        Willelmus bastardus</incipit><note> See Hardy, ut supra, iii (1871), pp. 174, 257, 289. </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  </msItem>
